%% Data Flow Diagram - Notebooks (Workbench Images)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as OpenShift Gateway/Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant AuthProxy as kube-rbac-proxy (3.x)<br/>oauth-proxy (2.x)<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Notebook as JupyterLab / Code Server<br/>8888/TCP or 8787/TCP HTTP
    participant DSP as Data Science Pipelines API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant PipeCtrl as Pipeline Controller
    participant Runtime as Runtime Image Pod
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant Quay as quay.io/modh/*<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OCP as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: User Opens Workbench
    User->>Gateway: HTTPS/443<br/>OpenShift OAuth
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: HTTPS/8443<br/>Bearer Token / OAuth
    AuthProxy->>Notebook: HTTP/8888 or 8787<br/>plaintext (localhost)<br/>Trusted sidecar

    Note over Notebook,S3: Flow 2: Elyra Pipeline Execution
    Notebook->>DSP: HTTPS/443<br/>Bearer Token<br/>Submit pipeline
    DSP->>PipeCtrl: Schedule pipeline run
    PipeCtrl->>Runtime: Create runtime pod<br/>ServiceAccount
    Runtime->>S3: HTTPS/443<br/>AWS credentials<br/>Artifact storage

    Note over Operator,Quay: Flow 3: Image Deployment by Operator
    Operator->>Operator: Process kustomize manifests<br/>(overlays/additional)
    Operator->>OCP: Create ImageStream CRs
    OCP->>Quay: HTTPS/443<br/>Pull secret<br/>Import images

    Note over Notebook,OCP: Runtime: oc CLI from Notebook
    Notebook->>OCP: HTTPS/443<br/>ServiceAccount token<br/>Cluster interaction
